2. Cu hnh Maven chy JSP

Trong pom.xml, bn cn b sung cu hnh JSP nh sau:

Thm dependency Tomcat Embed Jasper + JSTL

xml
<dependencies>
    <!-- JSP Support -->
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.apache.tomcat.embed</groupId>
        <artifactId>tomcat-embed-jasper</artifactId>
    </dependency>

    <dependency>
        <groupId>jakarta.servlet</groupId>
        <artifactId>jakarta.servlet-api</artifactId>
        <scope>provided</scope>
    </dependency>

    <!-- JSTL -->
    <dependency>
        <groupId>jakarta.servlet.jsp.jstl</groupId>
        <artifactId>jakarta.servlet.jsp.jstl-api</artifactId>
    </dependency>

    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.glassfish.web</groupId>
        <artifactId>jakarta.servlet.jsp.jstl</artifactId>
    </dependency>
</dependencies>

xml
<packaging>war</packaging>

5. Kt ni MySQL vi JPA

To entity v d:

java
@Entity
@Data
@NoArgsConstructor
@AllArgsConstructor
public class User {
    @Id
    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)
    private Long id;

    private String name;
    private String email;
}

Repository:

java
public interface UserRepository extends JpaRepository<User, Long> {}

6. Vit Controller tr v JSP

java
@Controller
@RequestMapping("/users")
public class UserController {

    @Autowired
    private UserRepository userRepository;

    @GetMapping
    public String listUsers(Model model) {
        model.addAttribute("users", userRepository.findAll());
        return "user-list"; // maps to /WEB-INF/views/user-list.jsp
    }

    @GetMapping("/create")
    public String createForm(Model model) {
        model.addAttribute("user", new User());
        return "user-form";
    }

    @PostMapping("/create")
    public String createUser(@ModelAttribute User user) {
        userRepository.save(user);
        return "redirect:/users";
    }
}

ChatGPT said:

Di y l gii thch chi tit tng bc v:

Gii thch theo ng "vng i MVC" trong Spring Boot.

1. JSP Controller: Gi d liu nh th no?

Khi bn c form trong JSP:

jsp
<form action="/users/create" method="post">
    <input type="text" name="name"/>
    <input type="text" name="email"/>
    <button type="submit">Save</button>
</form>

Browser s to HTTP POST request n URL /users/create, km theo d liu:

ini
name=Giang&email=abc@gmail.com

Trong Controller, Spring MVC t ng nhn d liu:

Cch 1: Nhn tng field

java
@PostMapping("/create")
public String createUser(
        @RequestParam String name,
        @RequestParam String email
) {
    System.out.println("Name = " + name);
    System.out.println("Email = " + email);
    return "redirect:/users";
}

Cch 2: Nhn bng object (ph bin nht)

java
@PostMapping("/create")
public String createUser(@ModelAttribute User user) {
    System.out.println(user.getName());
    System.out.println(user.getEmail());
    return "redirect:/users";
}

Spring t nh x name="field" vo User.

2. Controller JSP: Tr d liu nh th no?

Controller tr d liu v JSP thng qua Model.

V d:

java
@GetMapping
public String listUsers(Model model) {
    List<User> list = userRepository.findAll();
    model.addAttribute("users", list);
    return "user-list";
}

Trong JSP:

jsp
<c:forEach var="u" items="${users}">
    ${u.name}
</c:forEach>

Spring s forward sang file:

bash
/WEB-INF/views/user-list.jsp

v inject ton b d liu trong model.

3. JSP c th x l logic khng? (Bn hi tch do.jsp)

Trong JSP c in (JSP 2.0 tr v trc), ngi ta hay tch:

  • user.jsp giao din

  • user.do.jsp cha logic (scriptlets: <% ... %>)

Nhng lu quan trng:
Spring MVC khng khuyn khch logic trong JSP!

V Spring mun logic phi nm Controller + Service, cn JSP ch dnh cho View.

Tuy nhin, nu bn mun "tch lp do.jsp" trong Spring Boot th c 2 cch chnh:

Cch 1 Dng JSTL + EL, khng dng scriptlet (an ton nht)

Logic nm Controller,
JSP ch x l trnh by bng JSTL:

user.jsp: giao din
user-data.jsp: fragment include load danh sch
Khng dng scriptlet <% %>

V d:

user.jsp

jsp
<jsp:include page="user-data.jsp"/>

user-data.jsp

jsp
<c:forEach var="u" items="${users}">
    <tr>
        <td>${u.name}</td>
        <td>${u.email}</td>
    </tr>
</c:forEach>

y l cch c khuyn dng nht trong Spring Boot.

Cch 2 Nu bn thc s mun user.do.jsp x l logic bng scriptlet

Khng khuyn ngh, nhng bn c th lm:

user.jsp

jsp
<jsp:include page="user.do.jsp"/>

user.do.jsp

jsp
<%
    String message = "Hello " + request.getParameter("name");
    request.setAttribute("msg", message);
%>

user.jsp (tip tc hin th)

jsp
${msg}

Nhc im ln:

  • Logic trn vo view kh maintain

  • Khng test c

  • Khng tun chun MVC

  • Spring Boot 3 khng cn h tr tt scriptlets

Vy Spring cho bn do.jsp theo phong cch MVC chun nh no?

Spring Boot chun theo m hnh:

scss
Controller    Service    JSP (View)

Nu mun tch nh bn hi (page.jsp v page.do.jsp),
Spring Boot khuyn ngh:

Lp .do = Controller hoc Service
page.jsp ch l view

V d:

user.do (tc Controller)

java
@GetMapping("/users")
public String doGetUsers(Model model) {
    model.addAttribute("users", userService.getAll());
    return "user";
}

user.jsp

jsp
<c:forEach var="u" items="${users}">
    ${u.name}
</c:forEach>

y l bn Spring MVC chnh tc.

TM LI

1 JSP gi d liu Controller

Thng qua form HTML Spring t nh x bng @RequestParam hoc @ModelAttribute.

2 Controller tr d liu JSP

Dng Model.addAttribute() v return "view".

3 do.jsp trong Spring Boot?

Khng dng scriptlet tch logic bng Controller / Services
JSP ch render bng JSTL + EL.

Bn mun demo code hon chnh theo kiu:

user.jsp + user-data.jsp (tch view)

hay

UserController.java + UserService.java (tch logic chun MVC)?

6. To Controller tr v JSP

java
@Controller
@RequestMapping("/users")
public class UserController {

    @Autowired
    private UserRepository repo;

    @GetMapping
    public String index(Model model) {
        model.addAttribute("users", repo.findAll());
        return "user-list";  // -> /WEB-INF/views/user-list.jsp
    }

    @GetMapping("/create")
    public String showCreateForm(Model model) {
        model.addAttribute("user", new User());
        return "user-form";
    }

    @PostMapping("/create")
    public String create(@ModelAttribute User user) {
        repo.save(user);
        return "redirect:/users";
    }
}

c config trn mt dng R rng Kh theo di khi di

H tr nhiu profile Tt Tt
Dng cho d n ln B ri Cc k ph hp
Kh nng li t li D li indent, space
Mc nh Spring Boot u tinTng ngTng ng

2. u im Nhc im

Khi nn dng properties

  • D n nh, CRUD n gin

  • t cu hnh

  • Bn mun cu hnh nhanh, t ri ro

  • Bn mi hc Spring Boot

  • Khng thch indent YAML

V d:

properties
server.port=8080
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/demo
spring.datasource.username=root
spring.datasource.password=1234

Rt r rng, d thy, kh sai.

Khi nn dng yaml

  • D n ln: microservices, nhiu module

  • C nhiu cu trc nested

  • Cn chia config theo khi d c

  • Mun qun l nhiu environment (dev, prod, staging)

V d:

yaml
server:
  port: 8080

spring:
  datasource:
    url: jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/demo
    username: root
    password: 1234
  jpa:
    hibernate:
      ddl-auto: update
    show-sql: true

p, phn khi r rng, d maintain.

3. YAML tt hn khi dng nhiu profile

V d:

yaml
spring:
  profiles:
    active: dev

---
spring:
  config:
    activate:
      on-profile: dev
  datasource:
    url: jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/devdb

---
spring:
  config:
    activate:
      on-profile: prod
  datasource:
    url: jdbc:mysql://prodserver:3306/realdb

Properties lm ging vy nhng di v xu hn.

1. To file docker-compose.yml cho MySQL

To file:

docker-compose.yml

Ni dung:

yaml
version: "3.8"

services:
  mysql:
    image: mysql:8.0
    container_name: mysql_spring
    restart: always
    environment:
      MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD: root
      MYSQL_DATABASE: springdb
    ports:
      - "3307:3306"
    volumes:
      - mysql_data:/var/lib/mysql
      - ./mysql-init:/docker-entrypoint-initdb.d

volumes:
  mysql_data:

Gii thch

  • MySQL chy trn port 3307 (bn c th i).

  • Database mc nh khi to container: springdb

  • Th mc ./mysql-init cha cc file .sql nu bn mun init d liu.

  • D liu DB c lu qua volume.

bash

4. (TU CHN) c file cu hnh DB t bn ngoi Docker

Bn mun chy Spring Boot v c file .properties t bn ngoi?

arduino
config/db.properties

properties
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3307/springdb
spring.datasource.username=root
spring.datasource.password=root

Khi chy jar:

bash

Spring Boot s u tin file ny hn application.properties.

5. (TU CHN) Dng Docker Compose + mi trng (khng cn config local)

Bn cng c th Spring c bin mi trng t Docker:

yaml
services:
  spring:
    image: your-spring-img
    depends_on:
      - mysql
    environment:
      SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL: jdbc:mysql://mysql:3306/springdb
      SPRING_DATASOURCE_USERNAME: root
      SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD: root

u im: Khng cn sa file config trong app.

6. (CAO CP) Mount file properties vo container Spring Boot

Nu bn mun Spring Boot chy bn trong Docker v c config t host,
to docker-compose:

yaml
services:
  spring:
    image: your-app-image
    container_name: spring_app
    ports:
      - "8080:8080"
    volumes:
      - ./config:/config
    environment:
      SPRING_CONFIG_ADDITIONAL_LOCATION: /config/db.properties
    depends_on:
      - mysql

File ./config/db.properties s override config trong container.

2. Cu hnh Spring Boot trong application.properties

y l cu hnh chun Spring Boot kt ni ti MySQL container:

properties
# ==========================
# SERVER CONFIG
# ==========================
server.port=8080

# ==========================
# MYSQL DOCKER CONNECTION
# ==========================
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3307/springdb?useSSL=false&allowPublicKeyRetrieval=true&useUnicode=true&characterEncoding=UTF-8
spring.datasource.username=root
spring.datasource.password=root
spring.datasource.driver-class-name=com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver

# ==========================
# JPA / HIBERNATE CONFIG
# ==========================
spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update
spring.jpa.show-sql=true
spring.jpa.properties.hibernate.format_sql=true

# (Tu chn) Fix timezone
spring.jpa.properties.hibernate.jdbc.time_zone=UTC

Gii thch:

To file:

java
package com.example.demo.model;

import jakarta.persistence.*;

@Entity
@Table(name = "users")  // tn bng trong MySQL
public class User {

    @Id
    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)
    private Long id;

    @Column(nullable = false, unique = true)
    private String username;

    @Column(nullable = false)
    private String password;

    private String fullName;

    // Constructor rng
    public User() {}

    // Constructor y 
    public User(String username, String password, String fullName) {
        this.username = username;
        this.password = password;
        this.fullName = fullName;
    }

    // Getter & Setter
    public Long getId() { return id; }
    public void setId(Long id) { this.id = id; }

    public String getUsername() { return username; }
    public void setUsername(String username) { this.username = username; }

    public String getPassword() { return password; }
    public void setPassword(String password) { this.password = password; }

    public String getFullName() { return fullName; }
    public void setFullName(String fullName) { this.fullName = fullName; }
}

Ti sao nn dng Lombok?

1. To BaseDAO (generic DAO)

java
package com.example.demo.dao;

import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;
import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;
import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;
import java.util.List;

@Transactional
public abstract class BaseDAO<T> {

    @PersistenceContext
    protected EntityManager em;

    private final Class<T> clazz;

    protected BaseDAO(Class<T> clazz) {
        this.clazz = clazz;
    }

    public T findById(Long id) {
        return em.find(clazz, id);
    }

    public List<T> findAll() {
        return em.createQuery("FROM " + clazz.getName(), clazz)
                 .getResultList();
    }

    public T save(T entity) {
        em.persist(entity);
        return entity;
    }

    public T update(T entity) {
        return em.merge(entity);
    }

    public void delete(Long id) {
        T entity = findById(id);
        if (entity != null) em.remove(entity);
    }
}

2. To DAO con k tha (UserDAO)

java
package com.example.demo.dao;

import com.example.demo.model.User;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Repository;

@Repository
public class UserDAO extends BaseDAO<User> {

    public UserDAO() {
        super(User.class);
    }

    public User findByUsername(String username) {
        return em.createQuery(
                "SELECT u FROM User u WHERE u.username = :username", User.class)
                .setParameter("username", username)
                .getSingleResult();
    }
}

u im ca cch ny

Bn kim sot hon ton query bng EntityManager
Ph hp vi m hnh DAO truyn thng
Mi logic CRUD chung nm trong BaseDAO

Hn ch

Khng tn dng c cc tnh nng Spring Data JPA (paging, sorting, query methods)
Phi t vit query nhiu hn

java
package com.example.demo.repository;

import org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository;
import org.springframework.data.repository.NoRepositoryBean;

@NoRepositoryBean
public interface BaseRepository<T, ID> extends JpaRepository<T, ID> {

    // Thm method chung nu mun
    default void deleteSafely(ID id) {
        if (existsById(id)) {
            deleteById(id);
        }
    }
}

import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;
import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;
import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;
import java.util.List;

@Transactional
public abstract class BaseDAO<T> {

    @PersistenceContext

    private final Class<T> clazz;

    protected BaseDAO(Class<T> clazz) {
        this.clazz = clazz;
    }

    public T findById(Long id) {

    }

                 .getResultList();
    }

    public T save(T entity) {
        em.persist(entity);
        return entity;
    }

    public T update(T entity) {
        return em.merge(entity);

2 To DAO con (UserDAO)

To file:

swift
src/main/java/com/example/demo/dao/UserDAO.java

java
package com.example.demo.dao;

import com.example.demo.model.User;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Repository;

@Repository
public class UserDAO extends BaseDAO<User> {

    public UserDAO() {
        super(User.class);
    }

    // Custom method ring cho User
    public User findByUsername(String username) {
        return em.createQuery(
                "SELECT u FROM User u WHERE u.username = :username", User.class)
                .setParameter("username", username)
                .getResultStream()
                .findFirst()
                .orElse(null);
    }
}

UserDAO k tha BaseDAO, c th thm method ring.

import com.example.demo.dao.UserDAO;
import com.example.demo.model.User;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Service;

@Service
public class UserService {

        this.userDAO = userDAO;
    }

    public User createUser(User user) {
        return userDAO.save(user);
    }

    public User updateUser(User user) {
        return userDAO.update(user);
    }

    public void deleteUser(Long id) {
        userDAO.delete(id);
    }

    public User getUser(Long id) {
        return userDAO.findById(id);
    }

    public List<User> getAllUsers() {
        return userDAO.findAll();
    }

    public User getByUsername(String username) {
        return userDAO.findByUsername(username);
    }
}

@Service
public class UserService {

        this.userRepository = userRepository;
    }

        return userRepository.save(user);
    }

    public User updateUser(User user) {
        return userRepository.save(user); // save = create/update

    public void deleteUser(Long id) {

        return userRepository.findAll();
    }

    public User getByUsername(String username) {
        return userRepository.findByUsername(username);
    }
}

2 To BaseEntity vi timestamp & metadata

To lp:

java
package pttk.demo.gara.common.entities;

import jakarta.persistence.*;
import lombok.Getter;
import lombok.Setter;
import org.hibernate.annotations.CreationTimestamp;
import org.hibernate.annotations.UpdateTimestamp;

import java.time.LocalDateTime;

@MappedSuperclass
@Getter
@Setter
public abstract class BaseEntity {

    @Column(updatable = false)
    @CreationTimestamp
    private LocalDateTime createdAt;

    @UpdateTimestamp
    private LocalDateTime updatedAt;

    @Column(nullable = true)
    private String createdBy;

    @Column(nullable = true)
    private String updatedBy;
}

Gii thch:

  • @MappedSuperclass BaseEntity khng to table ring, nhng cc field s inherit cho entity con.

  • @CreationTimestamp t ng gn thi gian to.

  • @UpdateTimestamp t ng gn thi gian update.

  • createdBy / updatedBy optional, dng cho audit (user thao tc).

Warning ny xut hin v Lombok thy bn c class con k tha t BaseEntity, m bn dng @Data trn class con (User).

  • @Data t ng generate equals() / hashCode().

  • Theo mc nh, Lombok mun gi equals/hashCode ca superclass nu class ny k tha (callSuper=true).

  • Nu bn khng mun gi superclass, Lombok bo warning v ngh:

java
@EqualsAndHashCode(callSuper=false)

1 Cch gii quyt

Option A Gi superclass (khuyn ngh)

java

@EqualsAndHashCode(callSuper=true)
@NoArgsConstructor
@AllArgsConstructor
@Builder
@Entity
@Table(name = "users")
public class User extends BaseEntity {
    // fields...
}

  • callSuper=true equals/hashCode bao gm cc field t BaseEntity (createdAt, updatedAt...).

  • Thng dng khi BaseEntity c cc field quan trng, nh id hoc timestamp.

Option B Khng gi superclass

java

@EqualsAndHashCode(callSuper=false)
@NoArgsConstructor
@AllArgsConstructor
@Builder
@Entity
@Table(name = "users")
public class User extends BaseEntity {
    // fields...
}

  • callSuper=false equals/hashCode ch da trn cc field trong User, b qua BaseEntity.

  • Dng khi BaseEntity khng quan trng cho equals/hashCode, v d ch cha timestamp.

2 Li khuyn

  • Nu BaseEntity c id hoc cc field dng so snh entity dng callSuper=true.

  • Nu BaseEntity ch cha metadata / audit (createdAt, updatedAt, createdBy...) callSuper=false l OK.
